                            <h3>Time-To-Market</h3>
                            <table>
                                <tbody>
                                    <tr>
                                        <th><strong>KVM</strong></th>
                                        <th><strong>Measuring</strong></th>
                                    </tr>
                                    <tr>
                                        <td class="kvm_name"><span>Release Frequency</span> </td>
                                        <td><span>The time needed to satisfy
                                                the customer with effective products and services.</span></td>
                                    </tr>
                                    <tr>
                                        <td class="kvm_name"><span>Release
                                                Stabilization</span></td>
                                        <td><span>Impact of poor development
                                                practices and underlying design and code base.</span></td>
                                    </tr>
                                    <tr>
                                        <td class="kvm_name"><span>Cycle Time</span></td>
                                        <td><span>The time (including
                                                stabilization) to satisfy a key set of customers or to respond to a
                                                significant organizational request.</span></td>
                                    </tr>
                                    <tr>
                                        <td class="kvm_name"><span>Build and Integration Frequency</span></td>
                                        <td><span>Integrated and tested builds per Time Periods</span></td>
                                    </tr>
                                    <tr>
                                        <td class="kvm_name"><span>Mean Time to Repair</span></td>
                                        <td><span>Efficiency to Resolve errors = Average(Time when detected - Time when resolved) </span></td>
                                    </tr>
                                    <tr>
                                        <td class="kvm_name"><span>Lead Time</span></td>
                                        <td><span>The amount of time from when an idea is proposed or hypothesis is formed until a customer can benefit from that idea</span></td>
                                    </tr>
                                    <tr>
                                        <td class="kvm_name"><span>Lead Time for Changes</span></td>
                                        <td><span>THe amount of time to go from code-committed to code running in production</span></td>
                                    </tr>
                                    <tr>
                                        <td class="kvm_name"><span>Deployment Frequency</span></td>
                                        <td><span>The number of time that the organization deployed a new version of the product to users/customers</span></td>
                                    </tr>
                                    <tr>
                                        <td class="kvm_name"><span>Time to Restore Service</span></td>
                                        <td><span>Amount of time between the start of an outage and it's restoration</span></td>
                                    </tr>
                                    <tr>
                                        <td class="kvm_name"><span>Time-to-Learn</span></td>
                                        <td><span>The total time needed to Sketch an idea or improvement, build it, deliver it to users and learn from their usage</span></td>
                                    </tr>
                                    <tr>
                                        <td class="kvm_name"><span>Time to remove impediment</span></td>
                                        <td><span>Average time to raise an impediment and resolve it. Contributes to lead time and employee satisfaction</span></td>
                                    </tr>
                                    <tr>
                                        <td class="kvm_name"><span>Time to Pivot</span></td>
                                        <td><span>A measure of true business agility that presents the elapsed time between when an organization receives feedback and when it responds to the feedback</span></td>
                                    </tr>
                                </tbody>
                            </table>
                            <h3>Ability-to-Innovate</h3>
                            <table>
                                <tbody>
                                    <tr>
                                        <th><strong>KVM</strong></th>
                                        <th><strong>Measuring</strong></th>
                                    </tr>
                                    <tr>
                                        <td class="kvm_name"><span>On-Product Index</span></td>
                                        <td><span>The time developers are allowed to work on exactly one initiative. The less context-switching the better. Think Little's Law.</span></td>
                                    </tr>
                                    <tr>
                                        <td class="kvm_name"><span>Installed Version
                                                Index</span></td>
                                        <td><span>Because of the difficulty
                                                customers face adapting or changing to a new release.</span></td>
                                    </tr>
                                    <tr>
                                        <td class="kvm_name"><span>Usage Index</span></td>
                                        <td><span>Determines a product that
                                                is burdensome and difficult to use and excess software that must be
                                                maintained even if rarely used.</span></td>
                                    </tr>
                                    <tr>
                                        <td class="kvm_name"><span>Innovation Rate</span></td>
                                        <td><span>Growth of technical debt
                                                caused by poorly designed and developed software. Consequently, trend of
                                                budget percentage being consumed keeping old software alive.</span></td>
                                    </tr>
                                    <tr>
                                        <td class="kvm_name"><span>Technical Debt</span></td>
                                        <td><span>Additionally, measures
                                                increasingly poor-quality software that leads to greater
                                                resource.</span></td>
                                    </tr>
                                    <tr>
                                        <td class="kvm_name"><span>Defect Trends</span></td>
                                        <td><span>Measurement in the change in defects since the last measurement</span></td>
                                    </tr>
                                    <tr>
                                        <td class="kvm_name"><span>Production Incident Count</span></td>
                                        <td><span>The number of times in a given period that the Development team was interrupted to fix a problem in a released product. Indicates the stability of the product.</span></td>
                                    </tr>
                                    <tr>
                                        <td class="kvm_name"><span>Active Product Branches</span></td>
                                        <td><span>The number of different versions or variations of the Product. Indicates the potential impact of changes and the resulting complexity of work</span></td>
                                    </tr>
                                    <tr>
                                        <td class="kvm_name"><span>Time Spent Merging Code Between Branches</span></td>
                                        <td><span>The amount of time spent applying changes across different versions of a product or service</span></td>
                                    </tr>
                                    <tr>
                                        <td class="kvm_name"><span>Time spent context-switching</span></td>
                                        <td><span>Time lost to interruptions, time spent switching between tasks, etc.</span></td>
                                    </tr>
                                    <tr>
                                        <td class="kvm_name"><span>Change Failure Rate</span></td>
                                        <td><span>The percentage of released product changes that result in degraded service or require remediation</span></td>
                                    </tr>
                                </tbody>
                            </table>

